-- Norway's new homes sales down 15 pct yr/yr in Feb -Home builders
-- 
-- Mon Mar 17, 2014 06:03AM EDT
-- None



OSLO, March 17 (Reuters) - The sale of new Norwegian homes fell by 15 percent in February compared to the same month in 2013, the Norwegian Home Builders' Association said on Monday.

Housing starts for the same period fell by 14 percent, it added. Norway's housing market has struggled since last summer and most forecasters expect housing prices to ease slightly this year.